<section class="page-header">
    <h1>The Future of Governance</h1>
    <p>Where COR0110268.11P is heading as governance itself evolves.</p>
</section>

<section class="content-block">
    <h2>Autonomous and Semi‑Autonomous Governance</h2>
    <p>As systems become more autonomous, governance must be able to operate at machine speed while preserving human oversight. COR is designed to support hybrid models where humans and machines share governance responsibilities.</p>
</section>

<section class="content-block">
    <h2>Global and Cross‑Jurisdictional Governance</h2>
    <p>Future governance will span borders, regulations, and cultures. The engine’s modular structure allows multiple governance regimes to coexist, overlap, and be reconciled where necessary.</p>
</section>

<section class="content-block">
    <h2>Continuous Evolution</h2>
    <p>Governance is never finished. COR is built to be updated, extended, and reconfigured as new standards, risks, and technologies emerge.</p>
</section>
